The triangle inequalities are: 1. \( x + f(y) > f(y + f(x) - 1) \) 2. \( x + f(y + f(x) - 1) > f(y) \) 3. \( f(y) + f(y + f(x) - 1) > x \) We tested various functions and found that constant functions and linear functions with a constant term do not satisfy the triangle inequalities for all \( x \) and \( y \).
